This paper is about measuring network flow sizes, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI). The paper also discusses network forensics and security, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (CR). The use of counter braids, a novel counter architecture, involves data structures (DS). The paper also mentions the use of a Maximum Likelihood (ML) algorithm, which is related to information theory (IT). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency and accuracy of the proposed method, which is related to systems and control (SI).
